This paper deals with sentiment analysis of tweets, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of emoticons and adjectives/adverbs for classification suggests a focus on machine learning techniques, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
